window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Jaxon Pace should be celebrating. </p> <p>After all, he's the Don Supreme of most powerful and feared mafia in the city of Chicago, and he has just married the love of his life, Natalie Tyler.</p> <p>But the truth is Jaxon has been shaken to his core.</p> <p>Rescued seconds before a Don Council coup, he has just learned that the man he trusted most in the world has been lying to him his entire life. He trusts no one, and his concerns for the safety of his new wife and daughter grow by the hour. </p> <p>Especially when he learns that Michael Valentine, the presumed-dead and psychopathic head of the Two Headed Dragon, is very much alive and is out for blood. <i>His</i> blood. </p> <p>What's more, a rogue FBI agent now stalks Jaxon's every move, insisting that there is far more is going on within the crime syndicate than Jaxon is aware of.</p> <p>Jaxon will not rest until these threats are eliminated. But the question is, can he keep control of his city while managing to stay two steps ahead of the monsters now gunning for his family? Or will he lose <i>everything</i>?</p>"; 
